== Rice ==

Boil a half-full #kettle{}.

Pour the boiled water into a large #saucepan{} with @salt{1/4%tsp} on high heat. Add the @Basmati Rice{150%grams} and cook for ~{10-12%minutes}.

Once cooked, drain in a #sieve{} and pop back in the pan. Cover with a #lid{} and leave to the side until ready to serve.

== Teriyaki Peanut Chicken ==

While the rice cooks, heat a large #frying pan{} on medium-high heat with a drizzle of @oil{}.

Once hot, add the @Diced British Chicken Breast{260%grams} and stir-fry until browned all over, ~{5-6%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw chicken and its packaging.

Meanwhile, halve, peel and thinly slice the @Red Onion{1}(peeled and thinly sliced). Trim the @Green Beans{80%grams} and cut into thirds.

Once the chicken has browned, stir in the onion and green beans. Stir-fry until the veg has softened, ~{3-4%minutes}.

While everything cooks, peel and grate the @Garlic Clove{1}(peeled and grated).

Once the veg has softened, add the garlic and stir-fry for ~{1%minute}.

Stir the @Teriyaki Sauce{150%grams} into the pan along with the @Water{50%milliliters} for the sauce.

Lower the heat and simmer until the sauce is sticky, the beans are tender and the chicken is cooked through, ~{3-4%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: The chicken is cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Meanwhile, roughly crush the @Salted Peanuts{25%grams} in the unopened sachet with a #rolling pin{}.

Taste the sauce and season with @salt{} and @pepper{} if needed. Add a splash of water if it needs loosening, then remove from the heat.

Fluff up the rice with a #fork{} and serve with the teriyaki chicken on top. Sprinkle over the peanuts to finish.

Enjoy!